EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend local law number 115 for the year 2005, relating to child fatalities, in relation to a child fatality review advisory team.
EventItemMatterName: Child fatality review advisory team.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, Lauren’s Law, S.7103/A.10039, legislation that would require mandatory registration or declination of registration in the organ donor registry.
EventItemMatterName: Require mandatory registration or declination of registration in the organ donor registry. (S.7103/A.10039)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would amend the Penal Law to create the crime of staging a motor vehicle accident.
EventItemMatterName: Create the crime of staging a motor vehicle accident.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to fines for failures to comply with commercial waste disposal policies.
EventItemMatterName: Fines for failures to comply with commercial waste disposal policies.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Department of Education to convene a task force to review the outreach practices and graduate outcomes at institutions with gainful employment programs in New York State.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Education to convene a task force to review the outreach practices and graduate outcomes at institutions with gainful employment programs in NYS.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and local law number 63 for the year 2005, relating to tracking and reporting by the department of health and mental hygiene, in relation to requiring such department to track and report deaths of homeless persons in the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to track and report deaths of homeless persons in the NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of guidelines for traffic calming devices.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of guidelines for traffic calming devices.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring fencing on pedestrian passageways elevated over vehicular or pedestrian right of ways.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring fencing on pedestrian passageways elevated over vehicular or pedestrian right of ways.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R.2966/S.1176, the American Horse Slaughter Prevention Act of 2011.
EventItemMatterName: American Horse Slaughter Prevention Act of 2011. (H.R.2966/S.1176)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to disclosing the energy and water efficiency in dwelling units, co-ops and condominiums in buildings under fifty thousand square feet.
EventItemMatterName: Disclosing the energy and water efficiency in dwelling units, co-ops and condominiums in buildings under fifty thousand square feet.

EventItemMatterName: Reporting of deficiencies in Department of Homeless Services adult and family shelters, and to repeal subdivision e of section 21-312.
